==Russian==
===Etymology===
Supposedly from [[Tatar]] [[әйдә]].

===Verb===
'''айда''' (ajdá)

#{{ru-colloquial}} [[let]] [[us]] [[go]]
#:Хватит работать, '''айда''' по домам. — Enough of the work, let's go home.
#{{ru-colloquial}} [[made]] [[off]]; [[dashed]] [[away]]; [[vanished]]
#:Мы поругались, он собрал вещички и '''айда'''. — We had a quarrel, then he got his belongings and left.

====Usage note====
The verb has no conjugation and is used mostly as if in the [[imperative]]. In Russian grammar '''айда''' does not count as a true verb and is considered to be closer to a [[particle]].

